# 🚀 Fix Step-by-Step (DO THIS EXACTLY)

## ✅ Step 1: Verify image manually on mirror

Run from bastion/node:

```bash
podman pull bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/ose-local-storage-diskmaker-rhel9@sha256:5306e6aa51b219d20c09934a30c48a84eb5bcb9a5543cee35eacf08de9cd9943
```

👉 If this fails → image not mirrored

---

## ✅ Step 2: Check your mirror mapping (VERY IMPORTANT)

```bash
oc get imagedigestmirrorset -o yaml
```

OR

```bash
oc get imagecontentsourcepolicy -o yaml
```

👉 Look for wrong paths like:

```
openshift4/openshift4 ❌
```

---

## ❗ Step 3: Fix mirror config

Your mirror likely created wrong repo structure.

### Correct structure should be:

```
bastion:8443/ocp4/openshift4/<image>
```

NOT:

```
bastion:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift4/<image> ❌
```

---

## ✅ Step 4: Re-run mirror (most important fix)

On mirror host:

```bash
oc mirror --config imageset-config.yaml docker://bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443
```

Make sure your `ImageSetConfiguration` includes:

* ✅ platform (release)
* ✅ operators (VERY IMPORTANT — your missing part)

Example:

```yaml
mirror:
  platform:
    channels:
      - name: stable-4.19
  operators:
    - catalog: registry.redhat.io/redhat/redhat-operator-index:v4.19
```

👉 Your issue = **operator images not mirrored**

---

## ✅ Step 5: Apply IDMS/ITMS again

After mirroring:

```bash
oc apply -f idms-oc-mirror.yaml
oc apply -f itms-oc-mirror.yaml
```

---

## ✅ Step 6: Restart failing pods

```bash
oc get pods -A | grep -i pull | awk '{print $1, $2}' | while read ns pod; do
  oc delete pod $pod -n $ns
done
```

